  "steps": [
    {
      "order": 1,
      "instruction": "Preheat oven to 390F/200C."
    },
    {
      "order": 2,
      "instruction": "Finely mince ONE red chili (~1 tbsp). Combine chili, ginger, garlic, oil, 1/2 cup cilantro/coriander, salt and pepper in a small bowl and set aside."
    },
    {
      "order": 3,
      "instruction": "Rinse and pat the chicken dry (inside and out) with paper towels. Starting from the neck end of the chicken, use a teaspoon upside down to loosen the skin from the meat across the surface of the chicken (i.e. not the legs or wings). Just go as far as you can."
    },
    {
      "order": 4,
      "instruction": "Spoon the cilantro/mixture between the meat and the skin near neck. Use the spoon to spread it a bit, then to finish it off, use your finger/hands ON the skin to spread the mixture as far and evenly as you can. Doesn't need to be perfect! :)"
    },
    {
      "order": 5,
      "instruction": "Place the chicken stock/broth, kaffir lime leaves, lemongrass and the whole red chili into a dutch oven or baking tray. (Note 4)"
    },
    {
      "order": 6,
      "instruction": "Place the chicken in the broth, cover with a lid and roast for 45 minutes. Remove the lid, add the coconut milk and potatoes then roast for a further 30 minutes, or until juices run clear when pierced."
    },
    {
      "order": 7,
      "instruction": "Remove the chicken from the broth and cover loosely with foil to rest for 5 minutes."
    },
    {
      "order": 8,
      "instruction": "Skim excess fat off the surface of the broth - I usually get about 5 tbsp of fat off."
    },
    {
      "order": 9,
      "instruction": "Add the juice from the lime, sugar and fish sauce. Stir until the sugar is dissolved. Add remaining cilantro/coriander."
    },
    {
      "order": 10,
      "instruction": "Serve the chicken with the broth in a pouring jug, or cut up the chicken and serve it in the broth."
    }
  ]
}